Today Heavy Down Fall In  market Due To Panic Situations In Global, As I Told Yesterday, It's natural to worry when foreign stock markets take a big drop. But ups and downs in the market happen all the time, and they're normal. While what happens in other countries can affect the Indian stock market, it doesn't always happen the same way here.
Sometimes, when foreign markets go down, it can actually be a good time to buy stocks in India. India's economy and the way our market works are different from other places. So even if things look bad abroad, it might not be as bad here.
Overall, it's smart to keep an eye on what's happening globally, but we should focus on the strengths of India's economy. With careful investing and spreading our investments, we can manage through market ups and downs and keep aiming for profits in the Indian stock market.

Meaning of stock market crash 💥

5% Fall       :  Pullback
10% Fall     :  Correction
20% Fall     :  Bear Market
>30% Fall   :  Crash
>50% Fall   :  Recession

So right now Indian Market has not even reached PULLBACK.

US Market (Nasdaq) has entered CORRECTION.

Japan’s (Nikkei) Market has entered BEAR MARKET.

India Market has just touched the Pull Back stage.
